<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<rss version="2.0" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><channel><title>救生艇新闻：博客——保护人类</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/</link><description></description><lastBuildDate>Sat, 25 Apr 2026 12:39:36 GMT</lastBuildDate><generator>rfeed v1.1.1</generator><docs>https://github.com/svpino/rfeed/blob/master/README.md</docs><item><title>了解生物学的动画教科书</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/animated-textbooks-for-understanding-biology</link><description>&lt;img src="https://politepol.com/fd/NjxHZtldG2if.xml" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Sat, 25 Apr 2026 12:39:33 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/animated-textbooks-for-understanding-biology</guid></item><item><title>游动藻类的 3D 记录</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/3d-recordings-of-swimming-algae</link><description>对游动微生物周围 3D 流体流动的测量可以帮助研究人员更好地了解此类微生物的游动动力学。&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/3d-recordings-of-swimming-algae.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Sat, 25 Apr 2026 12:24:33 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/3d-recordings-of-swimming-algae</guid></item><item><title>“天鹰助推器”挑战脉冲星风星云粒子加速的理论极限</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/aquila-booster-challenges-theoretical-limits-of-particle-acceleration-in-pulsar-wind-nebulae</link><description>大型高空空气簇射天文台 (LHAASO) 已检测到 PeV (10 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/aquila-booster-challenges-theoretical-limits-of-particle-acceleration-in-pulsar-wind-nebulae.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Sat, 25 Apr 2026 12:09:33 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/aquila-booster-challenges-theoretical-limits-of-particle-acceleration-in-pulsar-wind-nebulae</guid></item><item><title>碳纳米管正在缩小铜电导率的差距</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/carbon-nanotubes-are-closing-the-gap-on-copper-conductivity</link><description>许多观察人士认为，碳纳米管这项技术并没有达到 20 世纪 90 年代末首次出现时对其进行的极端炒作。当时，人们对它们非凡的电学、热学和机械性能非常重视，并预测它们将彻底改变材料科学、电子学和日常生活。但我们能否更接近实现这一承诺呢？ &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/carbon-nanotubes-are-closing-the-gap-on-copper-conductivity2.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Sat, 25 Apr 2026 11:54:33 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/carbon-nanotubes-are-closing-the-gap-on-copper-conductivity</guid></item><item><title>检测极其稀有的六十分之一同位素的新方法也可以加强暗物质搜索</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/new-approach-to-detect-ultra-rare-part-per-sextillion-isotopes-could-also-sharpen-dark-matter-searches</link><description>同位素（具有不同中子数量的同一元素的原子）的探测和研究可以扩大物理研究的范围并实现新的科学发现。到目前为止，稀有同位素主要是使用加速器质谱（AMS）技术来检测的，该技术可以加速原子，然后测量它们的质量和电荷。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/new-approach-to-detect-ultra-rare-part-per-sextillion-isotopes-could-also-sharpen-dark-matter-searches2.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Sat, 25 Apr 2026 11:39:33 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/new-approach-to-detect-ultra-rare-part-per-sextillion-isotopes-could-also-sharpen-dark-matter-searches</guid></item><item><title>高分辨率成像揭示纳米级核组织</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/high-resolution-imaging-shines-light-on-nanoscale-nuclear-organization</link><description>印度科学研究所 (IISc) 的研究人员采用了一种先进的显微镜技术，能够以令人难以置信的高分辨率同时观察癌细胞核内的多个生物分子。他们可视化的生物分子包括细胞转录机制的关键成分和为细胞核提供结构支持的蛋白质——提供了最早的核组织详细图谱之一。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/high-resolution-imaging-shines-light-on-nanoscale-nuclear-organization2.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Sat, 25 Apr 2026 11:24:33 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/high-resolution-imaging-shines-light-on-nanoscale-nuclear-organization</guid></item><item><title>超细光纤表面附近的光可以对扭曲的纳米颗粒进行分类</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/light-near-surface-of-ultra-thin-optical-fibers-can-sort-twisted-nanoparticles</link><description>世界上许多重要的物体可以根据其手性或旋手性分为两类，包括对生命重要的分子，例如氨基酸。这种手性物体（正式定义为与其镜像不相同的物体）通常以在给定方向上扭曲的结构为特征。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/light-near-surface-of-ultra-thin-optical-fibers-can-sort-twisted-nanoparticles.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Sat, 25 Apr 2026 11:09:33 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/light-near-surface-of-ultra-thin-optical-fibers-can-sort-twisted-nanoparticles</guid></item><item><title>重新设计的人类细胞增强了跨多个传递系统的基因编辑粒子效力</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/re-engineered-human-cells-boost-gene-editing-particle-potency-across-multiple-delivery-systems</link><description>基因编辑已成为针对疾病遗传原因的一种强大方法，但以治疗所需的规模高效、安全地将编辑机制引入正确的细胞仍然是该领域最大的挑战之一。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/re-engineered-human-cells-boost-gene-editing-particle-potency-across-multiple-delivery-systems.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Sat, 25 Apr 2026 10:54:33 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/re-engineered-human-cells-boost-gene-editing-particle-potency-across-multiple-delivery-systems</guid></item><item><title>利用新型一体式光催化助催化剂简化清洁氢气的生产</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/simplifying-clean-hydrogen-production-with-a-new-all-in-one-photocatalytic-cocatalyst</link><description>研究人员展示了第一个用于光催化整体水分解的“一体式”助催化剂，这是一项可以简化清洁氢燃料生产的突破。这一发现标志着朝着利用阳光和水产生氢气的实用技术迈出了重要一步，氢气是一种关键的能源载体，预计将在建设脱碳和可持续社会中发挥重要作用。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/simplifying-clean-hydrogen-production-with-a-new-all-in-one-photocatalytic-cocatalyst2.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Sat, 25 Apr 2026 10:39:33 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/simplifying-clean-hydrogen-production-with-a-new-all-in-one-photocatalytic-cocatalyst</guid></item><item><title>自然语言人工智能帮助化学家一步步设计分子</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/natural-language-ai-helps-chemists-design-molecules-step-by-step</link><description>设计分子是化学最复杂的挑战之一。从救生药物到先进材料，每种化合物都需要精确的反应顺序。规划这些步骤需要技术知识和战略洞察力，这使得它成为一项通常依赖多年经验的任务。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/natural-language-ai-helps-chemists-design-molecules-step-by-step2.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Sat, 25 Apr 2026 10:24:33 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/natural-language-ai-helps-chemists-design-molecules-step-by-step</guid></item></channel></rss>